BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 541.20 Tm (Here's the core idea of today. A web service is a way for two applications to exchange data over a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 526.20 Tm (network, regardless of the language or platform either one is written in. The key word is data. Look) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 511.20 Tm (at the contrast on screen. A traditional web app, on the left, returns HTML - a page meant for a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 496.20 Tm (human's eyes in a browser. A web service, on the right, returns data - JSON or XML - meant for) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 481.20 Tm (another program to consume. Same server technology underneath, completely different audience.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 466.20 Tm (So when we build a REST API today, we're building the right-hand side: something that hands) Tj ET
