BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 397.40 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 381.40 Tm (There are two main ways to build web services. SOAP is the older, heavier, XML-based standard.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 366.40 Tm (REST is the lighter, more flexible style that dominates modern APIs - and the one we'll use. SOAP) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 351.40 Tm (isn't the villain; it's just from an earlier era. Read across the table: SOAP is a strict protocol with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 336.40 Tm (rigid rules; REST is an architectural style with guidelines. SOAP is XML-only; REST usually uses) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 321.40 Tm (JSON. SOAP is heavier and more verbose; REST is lightweight and fast. SOAP requires a formal) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 306.40 Tm (contract file called a WSDL; REST doesn't. In industry, REST is the standard for web, mobile, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 291.40 Tm (microservices. SOAP still lives in legacy banking and large enterprise systems where its strict) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 276.40 Tm (contracts were valued. You'll meet REST everywhere; SOAP occasionally in older codebases.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 261.40 3.00 142.00 re f
