BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (REST is defined by a set of constraints. You don't need to memorise all six today, but knowing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (they exist helps you understand why REST APIs are built the way they are. Stateless - every) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (request carries everything the server needs; the server keeps no memory between requests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (Client-server - the UI and the data are separate and evolve independently. Uniform interface - a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (consistent, predictable way to access resources. Cacheable - responses can declare whether they) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (may be stored and reused. Layered system - there can be intermediaries like load balancers and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (gateways without either side knowing. And code on demand, the one optional constraint, rarely) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (used.) Tj ET
