BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 500.20 Tm (A table mapping GET, POST, PUT, DELETE to Read, Create, Update, Delete with Student API examples.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 486.70 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 476.70 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 460.70 Tm (REST uses the standard HTTP methods as verbs describing what you want to do to a resource,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 445.70 Tm (and the four you'll use map directly onto the four database operations known as CRUD - Create,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 430.70 Tm (Read, Update, Delete. GET reads existing data - GET slash students lists all students. POST) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 415.70 Tm (creates new data - POST slash students adds a new student. PUT updates existing data - PUT) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 400.70 Tm (slash students slash id updates one. DELETE removes data - DELETE slash students slash id.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 385.70 Tm (Here's the mental model: think of a student record. You GET it to view, POST a new one when a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 370.70 Tm (student enrols, PUT to fix their email, and DELETE when they leave. Same noun - slash students -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 355.70 Tm (a different verb for each action. That's the whole idea of a REST API.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 340.70 3.00 142.00 re f
BT /F2 14.50 Tf 0.100 0.100 0.120 rg 1 0 0 1 58.00 324.70 Tm (Slide 10 - HTTP status codes) Tj ET
0.820 0.820 0.860 rg 58.00 307.70 496.00 1.20 re f
