BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 277.70 Tm (Colour-coded badges: 200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 404 Not Found, 500 Server Error.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 264.20 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 254.20 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 238.20 Tm (Every HTTP response carries a numeric status code telling the client what happened. There are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 223.20 Tm (dozens, but you only need five today. They're grouped: 2-hundreds mean success, 4-hundreds) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 208.20 Tm (mean the client made a mistake, 5-hundreds mean the server broke. 200 OK - the request worked;) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 193.20 Tm (Spring returns this by default for a successful GET. 201 Created - used after a successful POST;) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 178.20 Tm (you'll set it yourself with at-ResponseStatus. 400 Bad Request - the client sent something) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 163.20 Tm (malformed, like invalid JSON. 404 Not Found - the URL or resource doesn't exist, like asking for a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 148.20 Tm (student ID that isn't there. And 500 Server Error - something threw an unhandled exception in your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 133.20 Tm (code; we'll learn to handle these gracefully in Session 3.) Tj ET
