BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 677.50 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 661.50 Tm (A URI - the path part of a URL - names a resource. The golden rule of REST: URIs are nouns,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 646.50 Tm (HTTP methods are verbs. Don't put the action in the URL - let the method say what you're doing;) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 631.50 Tm (the URL just names what you're acting on. On the good side: slash students for the collection,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 616.50 Tm (slash students slash id for one student, and a query parameter like question-mark name equals) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 601.50 Tm (John for filtering. On the bad side: slash getStudent, slash deleteStudentById, slash student slash) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 586.50 Tm (fetch - the verb does not belong in the path. The pattern to internalise: plural nouns for collections,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 571.50 Tm (a path segment to identify one item, and query parameters for optional filtering. The verb is never) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 556.50 Tm (in the URL.) Tj ET
