BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 203.00 Tm (You used at-RestController in Session 1, but here's what it actually is under the hood. It's a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 188.00 Tm (convenience annotation bundling two others: at-Controller plus at-ResponseBody.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 173.00 Tm (At-ResponseBody is the important half. It tells Spring to take whatever your method returns and) Tj ET
