BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (By default, when you return a Student from a method, Spring sends it back with status 200 OK.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (But sometimes you need control over the full response - the status code, the headers, and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (body. That's what ResponseEntity gives you: it's a wrapper around the entire response. Look at) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (the panels. On the left, a raw return - the status is always 200, even if the student wasn't found.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (On the right, ResponseEntity - you return ResponseEntity dot ok with the student for 200, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (ResponseEntity dot notFound for 404, depending on the outcome. Reach for ResponseEntity) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (when you need different status codes depending on what happened - 201 Created after a POST,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (404 when something's missing, or to attach custom headers. It's the professional way to build) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 618.00 Tm (precise REST responses.) Tj ET
